<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>Who was Mary Elizabeth Lease, and what was her famous advice to farmers?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Raise more cattle, less corn</option>
            <option letter="b">Raise less corn and more hell</option>
            <option letter="c">Focus on industrial farming</option>
            <option letter="d">Abandon farming altogether</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Mary Elizabeth Lease was a prominent Populist speaker who urged farmers to "raise less corn and more hell," encouraging political activism.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>What was the "Crime of 1873"?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">A banking scandal</option>
            <option letter="b">A railroad monopoly</option>
            <option letter="c">The demonetization of silver</option>
            <option letter="d">A farm foreclosure crisis</option>
        </options>
        <answer>c</answer>
        <explanation>The "Crime of 1873" referred to Congress's decision to stop minting silver dollars, which Populists believed caused deflation and hurt farmers.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>What role did African American farmers play in the Populist movement?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">They were excluded entirely</option>
            <option letter="b">They formed separate but allied organizations</option>
            <option letter="c">They led the movement</option>
            <option letter="d">They opposed the movement</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>African American farmers formed their own Colored Farmers' Alliance, which worked parallel to but separately from the white Farmers' Alliance.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>What was the Populists' position on railroad ownership?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Complete privatization</option>
            <option letter="b">Government ownership</option>
            <option letter="c">State-level control</option>
            <option letter="d">Corporate self-regulation</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Populists advocated for government ownership of railroads to prevent monopolistic practices and ensure fair rates for farmers.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>What economic reform did Populists support to help farmers pay their debts?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Higher interest rates</option>
            <option letter="b">Gold standard</option>
            <option letter="c">Inflation through silver coinage</option>
            <option letter="d">Reduced farm production</option>
        </options>
        <answer>c</answer>
        <explanation>Populists supported the free coinage of silver to create inflation, which would make it easier for farmers to pay off their debts.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
